Class HP4140

  • java.lang.Object
    • icontrol.drivers.Device
      • icontrol.drivers.instruments.hp.HP4140

  • @iC_Annotation(CommPorts=GPIB,
               InstrumentClassName="HP 4140")
public class HP4140
extends Device
    Hewlett-Packard HP 4140B pA meter / DC voltage source.

    All device commands that the NewInstrument understands are implemented here.

    Instrument Commands:

    • Measure(String)
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    KPP (Kurt Pernstich: pernstich@alumni.ethz.ch)

      • Measure

        @AutoGUIAnnotation(DescriptionForUser="<html>TODO</html>",
                   ParameterNames="File Extension",
                   DefaultValues=".ui",
                   ToolTips="")
 @iC_Annotation(MethodChecksSyntax=false)
public void Measure(java.lang.String FileExtension)
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              throws java.io.IOException,
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     javax.script.ScriptException
        For Emily to test saving data of a long measurement. Starts a measurement and waits until the measurement is done. Then saves the data.

        Note that the first few measuremtn point might be lost becuase the 4140 drops them after a serial poll used to get the SRQ Status Byte (see Manual page 3-52, Note 2).

        Parameters:
        FileExtension -
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - re-thrown from SendToInstrument
        javax.script.ScriptException - When the data could not be saved to a file.
